reference:
  Gettext
  gettext




   &reftitle.intro;

     The gettext functions implement an NLS (Native Language Support)
     API which can be used to internationalize your PHP applications.
     Please see the gettext documentation for your system for a thorough
     explanation of these functions or view the docs at
     &url.gettext.docs;.





    &reftitle.required;


     To use these functions you must download and install the GNU gettext
     package from &url.gettext;





    &reftitle.install;


     To include GNU gettext support in your PHP build you must add the option
     --with-gettext[=DIR] where DIR is the
     gettext install directory, defaults to /usr/local.


     Note to Win32 Users

      In order to enable this module on a Windows environment, you must copy
      gnu_gettext.dll from the DLL folder of the PHP/Win32 binary
      package to the SYSTEM32 folder of your windows machine. (Ex: C:\WINNT\SYSTEM32
      or C:\WINDOWS\SYSTEM32)






    &reftitle.runtime;
    &no.config;




